## ðŸ† Test Scope Rules (User-Focused)

### What TO Test 
- âœ… **User-visible behavior and interactions**
- âœ… **Critical user flows** (happy path + 1-2 error cases)  
- âœ… **Integration points** where components connect
- âœ… **Accessibility and usability**
- âœ… **State changes** that affect user experience
- âœ… **Error handling** that users would encounter

### What NOT to Test
- âŒ **Implementation details** (internal function calls, state structure)
- âŒ **Every state combination** (focus on critical paths only)
- âŒ **Platform-specific edge cases** (unless critical for UX)
- âŒ **Library internals** (trust that React, Tamagui, etc. work)
- âŒ **Complex interaction chains** (convert to integration tests)
- âŒ **Internal hooks** (mock external dependencies only)

